# MMS connection phase — ACSE AARE (Associate Response), over TPKT/COTP/ISO-Session (ACCEPT SPDU).
# Real ICCP/TASE.2 PDU reassembled from a TCP-segmented capture (mms.cap frame 14), re-wrapped in
# eth/IPv4/TCP:102 via the codec. Only the hex is committed. The ISO 8327 ACCEPT SPDU (SI 14) carries the
# ISO 8823 Presentation CPA-type in its user-data (PGI 0xc1), which wraps the ACSE AARE (0x61) and the MMS
# initiate-response. The session/ACSE bytes are kept verbatim; only the ACSE APDU type is surfaced (AARE).

